Recoverable amounts are generally determined on the basis of fair values less costs to sell; 
in the segments Onshore Wind / Solar and Offshore Wind, they are also determined on the 
basis of values in use.

In fiscal 2023, RWE AG purchased a total of 421,816 RWE shares (previous year: 424,120) 
for a purchase price of €16,137,338.58 on the capital market (previous year: 
€16,794,705.09).

These activities primarily include the 
non-controlling interests in the German transmission system operator Amprion and in E.ON; 
the E.ON dividend is reported in the financial result.
